                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Hindalco priority to capacity expansion
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                             
	Mumbai, Sept. 3: Hindalco Industries will invest over Rs 10,000 crore this fiscal to expand its aluminium capacity as part of a plan to pump Rs 40,000 crore into various projects by 2014.         
	Chairman Kumar Mangalam Birla told shareholders at Hindalcos 51st AGM that the company was looking to expand the smelter capacity at Hirakud more than two-fold in phases.         
	The smelter expansion to 1.61 lakh tonnes from 1.55 lakh tonnes is in progress and will be completed in the second quarter of 2011. A further expansion to 2.13 lakh tonnes is expected to be completed by the fourth quarter of 2012.         
	The company is evaluating the possibility of amplifying the smelting capacity at Hirakud from the proposed 2.13 lakh tonnes to 3.60 lakh tonnes, he said.        
	All the new projects  Utkal Alumina, Mahan Aluminium, Aditya Alumina and Jharkhand Aluminium  are on course, Birla said.        
	These projects are expected to be commissioned between 2012 and 2014. The company has earmarked a capital expenditure of around Rs 40,000 crore.                                                                                                                                       
